GET     git clone https://github.com/hallwaykid/pw.git # or
        git clone http://repo.or.cz/w/www.git

        cd pw/ruby
INSTALL bundle install # dependencies
	./install      # symlink (rsync or build gem if you want)

        cd ..         # run here or link {css,js}
USE     foreman start # HTTP and HTTPS on 80/443
NOTES
 httpd.ru can be used to launch other Rack-API servers ('thin' is default, unicorn works well, etc)
 to listen on 80/443 (in lieu of >1024 behind apache/nginx/lighttpd)
 $ setcap cap_net_bind_service=+ep `which ruby`

HOST  mkdir domain/hostname
CLEAN rm -rf cache index
